Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.sql

Class ResultSetMapper<T>

java.lang.Object
nl.naturalis.common.sql.ResultSetMapper<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of the model bean
public abstract class ResultSetMapper<T>
extends Object
Maps a result set row to a model bean. This class does not have any public constructors. It is meant to be subclassed, with the subclass invoking its protected constructor.
Author:
Ayco Holleman

  • Constructor Details

    • ResultSetMapper

      protected ResultSetMapper​(Supplier<T> instanceFactory, Class<T> beanClass)
      Creates a new ResultSetMapper. Subclasses should create a no-arg constructor that calls this constructor. For example: 

       class DepartmentMapper extends ResultSetMapper {
   public DepartmentMapper() {
     super(Department::new, Department.class);
   }
 }
      Parameters:
      instanceFactory - A supplier of new instances of the model bean class
      beanClass - The model bean class

    • unmap

      public void unmap​(String... fields)
      Temporarily unmaps the specified fields. This can be useful when mapping SQL queries that SELECT only a few columns of the table or view corresponding to the bean class. The new mapping only applies to this instance of ResultSetMapper. Previously and subsequently instantiated instances will not be affected.
      Parameters:
      fields - The fields to unmap

    • unmapAllBut

      public void unmapAllBut​(String... fields)
      Temporarily unmaps all but the specified fields. This can be useful when mapping SQL queries that SELECT only a few columns of the table or view corresponding to the bean class. The new mapping only applies to this instance of ResultSetMapper. Previously and subsequently instantiated instances will not be affected.
      Parameters:
      fields - The fields to retain

    • nameMapper

      protected UnaryOperator<String> nameMapper()
      Provide a string operator that maps field names to result set column labels. By default a straight one-to-one mapping is used. The returned name mapping mechanism will be used for all instances of ResultSetMapper. Two alternative name mappers are provided in this package: CamelToSnake and CamelToSnakeUpperCase.
      Returns:
      A string operator that maps field names to result set column labels

    • notMapped

      protected Set<String> notMapped()
      Provide a set of field names that must remain unmapped. By default all fields will be mapped. The returned set will be used for all instances of ResultSetMapper.
      Returns:
      a set of field names that must remain unmapped

    • mapSpecial

      protected Map<String,​String> mapSpecial()
      Provide a map of field-to-column mappings that override the mapping mechanism provided by nameMapper(). The returned map will be used for all instances of ResultSetMapper.
      Returns:
      A map of field-to-column mappings that override the mapping mechanism provided by getNameMapper()
